Defendant Ronald Adam Victory in court, in custody.  Attorney Elizabeth A Longo in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Gillion Parham in court for Ronald Adam Victory.  JURY TRIAL, DAY 2 OF 2.  Case called with jury present 8:31am.  Court addresses comments to jury.  WITNESS:  Aaron Z.  State rests.  Jury excused.  Recess.  Reconvene without jury.  Court questions counsel re witnesses/testimony.  Jury now present.  WITNESS:  Dep C. Holman (WCSD). Court has side-bar with State and counsel.  WITNESS:  Dep C. Holman (continued).  Jury excused.  Court finds witness has violated sequestration order and prohibits testimony from said witness.  Recess.  Reconvene w/out jury.  Counsel indicates def wishes to testify. Court questions def.  Recess.  Reconvene w/out jury. Court questions def.  Def wishes to testify.  Court further questions def and finds def freely and voluntarily waives his right to remain silent. Discussion between Court and counsel as to def's prior record.  Court questions def again; def still wishes to testify. Jury present.  WITNESS:  Ronald V.  Jury excused. Court questions State and counsel.  Jury present.  Def rests.  WITNESS:  Aaron Z. (recalled).  Jury excused.  Jury instruction conference held between Court and counsel. Jury present.  Court reads partial Instructions to jury.  Closing statements.  Court reads conclusion of Instructions to jury.  Jury excused for deliberations at 11:55am.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  Court identifies foreperson.  Court reads verdict forms.  Jury finds def guilty on Ct 1 and guilty on Ct 2.  Court polls jurors as a group; def does not request jurors be polled individually.  Jurors thanked and released at 12:50pm.  State moves for judgment on Ct 1.  Def moves for judgment not withstanding verdict on Ct 1. Court issues judgment on verdicts in both counts.  Court orders PSI be prepared.  Court revokes bond pending sentencing.
